Heat oven to 375 degrees F. Grease baking sheets. Place sheets of foil on countertop for cooling cookies. Place brown sugar, shortening, egg, milk, orange peel and vanilla in large bowl. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended. Combine oats, flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cloves. Add to shortening mixture; beat at low speed just until blended. Stir in apples, raisins and walnuts. Drop dough by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto prepared baking sheets. Bake one baking sheet at a time at 375 degrees F for 10 to 12 minutes or until cookies are lightly browned. DO NOT OVERBAKE. Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet. Remove cookies to foil to cool completely.